\subsection{Visual Diagnostics: Fast-Slow Geometry and Tri-Height Evolution}
\label{subsec:visual_phase_space_ascii}

\paragraph{Phase-Space Topology (ASCII Schematic).}
The schematic below summarizes the dynamical pathways between the active sheet, unstable separatrix, and laminar floor in the reduced fast-slow space:
\begin{verbatim}
                         TURBULENCE SCALE (q = sqrt(e + delta))
                                      ^
                                      |
  (1) EVENING RUN-UP                  |       /  q_plus (Active Sheet: M0_act)
      High shear maintains            |      /
      q_plus branch balance.          |     /   <- SBL trajectory in active regime
                                      |    /
                                      |   *  FOLD CATASTROPHE
                                      |  /   Delta drops below Delta_fold = -beta^2/4.
  (2) SUDDEN COLLAPSE                 | /    Normal hyperbolicity lost.
      Trajectory drops on             |/
      fast timescale 1/epsilon.       * <--- q_minus (Unstable separatrix)
  ------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------> NET FORCING (Delta)
                                     /|
  (3) RE-IGNITION RECOVERY          / |  o========= q_lam = 0 (Laminar sheet)
      Shear rebuilds; at Delta=0,   /  |  (quiescent floor: e = -delta)
      q_lam turns repelling.       /   |
                                 v     |
                              TRANSCRITICAL IGNITION (Delta = 0)
\end{verbatim}

